cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a novel ECOC algorithm with a soft coding scheme based on centroid distance. The algorithm uses regressors as base learners and is evaluated on five UCI datasets. The paper's focus on machine learning and classification suggests that it is most likely to belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of Sequential Forward Floating Selection (SFFS) and the measure of coverage suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.DM (Data Mining) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
